&lt;p&gt;The Financial Controller will own several business functions and receive significant exposure to the organization. This is a newly created seat — an investment in building a stronger finance foundation. The Financial Controller will serve as a key thought partner on financial operations, process infrastructure, and business performance.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As an Controller, you will own all accounting, financial reporting, and budgeting processes while contributing to the growth and operational maturity of a high-growth, private equity-backed business. You will drive timely financial operations, implement scalable systems, and support audits and compliance. In addition, you will also be responsible for overseeing the day-to-day business operations of the organization including but not limited to employee management/administration, new business and growth initiatives, and contract administration. You will serve as a crucial operator and thought partner within the business both as a leader for its employees, as well as a representative of the holding company. We are looking for someone who is excited to own the numbers, excel in an entrepreneurial environment supported by proven playbooks, and who has a can-do attitude to truly operate and manage a growing business.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role will report to the CEO in South Carolina, and will be expected to work Eastern hours.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
